caption: Reference ID
description: The reference ID.

caption: Reference PID
description: The physical ID of the reference.

caption: Bibtex Key
description: An abbreviated identifier for the study in the format of an in-text citation, given by Bibtex, i.e. "Jones2013". A lowercase letter is appended to the date where multiple items may be confused.

caption: RefWorks ID
description: The corresponding RefWorks ID for the study

caption: Reference is Archived
description: Where TRUE, the reference is archived.

caption: Is Archived Reason
description: A reason why the reference was archived.

caption: Reference is Excluded from Data Extraction
description: Where TRUE, the reference was excluded from further data extraction.

caption: Excluded Reason
description: The reason(s) why the reference was excluded from further data extraction.

caption: Excluded Reason Type
description: The type of reason why the reference was excluded from further data extraction.

caption: Publisher
description: The publisher of the reference.

caption: Publisher (Alt.)
description: The name of the publisher at the time of publication, if different from publisher.

caption: Publication Year
description: The year of reference publication.

caption: DOI
description: The DOI associated with the reference, i.e. 10.3168/jds.2014-8432

caption: PMID
description: The eight-digit PMID associated with the reference, i.e. 84889799

caption: Title
description: The title of the reference.

caption: Author(s)
description: The author(s) of the reference.

caption: Abstract
description: The abstract of the reference.

caption: Source Country
description: The source country of the reference.

caption: Study Design
description: The type of study design reported in the reference.

caption: Study Design Description
description: A description of the study design reported in the reference.

caption: Sampling Method
description: A description of the sampling method reported in the reference.

caption: Found 2016
description: Where TRUE, the reference was captured in the iAM.AMR.SEARCH_2016 project.

caption: Found 2019
description: Where TRUE, the reference was captured in the iAM.AMR.SEARCH_2019 project.
The reference was captured in the 2019 literature search. It was initially included at secondary screening, but was later excluded at secondary screening during screening validation.

caption: Found Snowball
description: The reference was captured through snowballing (searching cited papers, and or reverse citations)

caption: Found Submit
description: The reference was captured through a direct submission to CEDAR

caption: Extracted by CEDAR Enterococcus Scoping Review
description: Specifies whether this reference was extracted by the ESR team (i.e. "Enterococcus Scoping Review"). References marked cedar_extract_esr = TRUE were either: a) identified by both the ESR and the 2019 literature search (and extracted by the ESR team) or b) identified by the ESR only.
True if identified by the August 2021 update to the search (focused on turkeys only)

caption: Has Explicit Breakpoints?
description: Specifies whether the study explicitly reports the MIC values used in its susceptibility tests

caption: Has MIC Table?
description: Specifies whether the study includes an MIC table

caption: AST Method
description: The antimicrobial susceptibility test type applied in the study

caption: Has Cattle
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Chicken
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Swine
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Turkey
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Enterococcus
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Salmonella
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).

caption: Has Campylobacter
description: The title or abstract of this reference contains keywords related to this topic (animal, or microbe).
The record was imported from CEDAR_v1 into CEDAR_v2.
The reference ID used within CEDAR v1. This only exists when the reference is an import from v1.
This reference exists in both v1 and v2.
For v2 references, this is the  v1 reference which matched during factor migration from v1 to v2. Factors were migrated from this record.
For v1 references, this is the v2 reference which matched during factor migration from v1 to v2. Factors were migrated to this record.
These are v2 references - with imported factors from a v1 match - that do not need to be dual extracted, as they were reviewed thoroughly by Ashley or Daniella in v1.
The ID of the m_reference_history table for the latest action entry
The ID of the last action associated with the reference in the v2 reference_history scheme. This is for migration to CW reference history and status.
The ID of the user who was associated with the last action in the v2 reference_history scheme. This is for migration to CW reference history and status
The foreign key from the reference_status table. This is being implemented in v3 (CEDAR Web).

caption: Factor ID
description: The factor ID.

caption: Factor PID
description: The physical ID of the factor.
The record version number (default: 1).

description: The reference that reports the factor.

caption: Archived?
description: Where TRUE, the factor is archived.
A reason why the factor was archived.
Where TRUE, the factor was excluded from further data extraction.
The reason(s) why the factor was excluded from further data extraction.

caption: Title
description: A title for the factor.

caption: Description
description: A description of the factor.

caption: Factor (exposed) Group
description: A brief description of the factor (i.e., exposed, case)  group.

caption: Comparator (un-exposed) Group
description: A brief description of the comparator (i.e., un-exposed, control, referent)  group.

caption: Stage (Allocated)
description: The production stage at which the groups were allocated (i.e. factor applied)

caption: Host
description: The host (level 1) from which the assayed samples were isolated.

caption: Host (sub-type)
description: The host (level 2) from which the assayed samples were isolated.

description: The production stream of the host.

caption: Host Life Stage
description: The life stage of the host.
The user that extracted the resistance outcome
The date at which the resistance outcome was extracted
The canonical resistance outcome ID. The URID is shared between resistance outcomes (ROs) that have been extracted in duplicate

caption: Archived?
description: Where TRUE, the resistance-outcome is archived.
A reason why the resistance-outcome was archived.

caption: AMR
description: The resistance that was assayed
The genomic resistance assayed as a measure of resistance

caption: Microbe
description: The microbe assayed for resistance
The subtype of the microbe assayed for resistance

caption: Stage Observed
description: The production stage at which the observations were recorded (i.e. factor observed)

caption: Grain/Type
description: The type of measure of association reported for the resistance outcome

caption: Result Unit
description: The experimental unit or level of analysis for which the measure of association is presented

caption: Location
description: The location of the resistance outcome data in-text, i.e. "Table 2". If the data is from the body of the text, use the page and paragraph numbers (Pg. and Para. respectively)

caption: Count of AMR(+) | Exposed
description: The number (count) of observations of resistance in the exposed group

caption: Count of AMR(-) | Exposed
description: The number (count) of observations of susceptibility in the exposed group

caption: Count of AMR(+) | Referent
description: The number (count) of observations of resistance in the referent group

caption: Count of AMR(-) | Referent
description: The number (count) of observations of susceptibility in the referent group

caption: Proportion of AMR(+) | Exposed
description: The proportion of observations of resistance in the exposed group, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Proportion of AMR(-) | Exposed
description: The proportion of observations of susceptibility in the exposed group, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Proportion of AMR(+) | Referent
description: The proportion of observations of resistance in the referent group, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Proportion of AMR(-) | Referent
description: The proportion of observations of susceptibility in the referent group, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Total Exposed
description: The total number of observations in the exposed group

caption: Total Referent
description: The total number of observations in the referent group

caption: OR
description: The odds ratio that describes the factor, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Lower CI
description: The lower (usually 95%) confidence interval of the odds ratio that describes the factor, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Upper CI
description: The upper (usually 95%) confidence interval of the odds ratio that describes the factor, up to 2 decimal places

caption: Sig.
description: The significance (p-value) associated with the odds ratio that describes the factor, i.e. "< 0.05". May include symbols, numbers, and letters. There is no significance associated with count or prevalence data, only Odds Ratios. If an odds ratio is provided, without a significance level, please report "NR" for "not reported"

caption: Confidence Level
description: The confidence level associated with the confidence interval (as a percentage, most commonly 95%)
The AST method used to assay resistance

description: The breakpoint version used to interpret the results of the AST.

The reference ID corresponding to this history entry. This was formerly a foreign key to the reference table. Since the reference table now has a foreign key for this table's primary id instead, the former foreign key to the reference table can no longer exist. Now that this reference_join_reference_history table is depreciated (purely a legacy table), the foreign key to the reference table is not necessary anyway.
